{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-03-05T14:48:44.820Z","role":"user","content":"You are continuing work on bead Forge-7ug in the forge repository.\n\n## Previous Attempt\n\nYour previous implementation had issues identified by the review:\n\nCould not parse structured verdict; defaulting to request_changes\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. Fix ALL the issues listed above\n2. Make sure the project builds and tests pass\n3. Commit your fixes with a clear message\n4. Push to the branch: forge/Forge-7ug\n\n## Original Task\n\n**Bead**: Forge-7ug\n**Title**: Fix bellows+reviewfix: wrong trigger, wrong API, no thread resolution\n\nBellows + reviewfix have multiple interconnected bugs that prevent automatic PR fix triggering. PR #2 (Forge-f4q) demonstrates all of them.\n\n## Bug 1 â€” Bellows trigger fires on wrong condition\n\nbellows.go: NeedsChanges() only returns true for review state \"CHANGES_REQUESTED\".\nCopilot (and many human reviewers) submit reviews as \"COMMENTED\" state with inline\nthread suggestions. These never trigger EventReviewChanges.\n\nFix: Add a new prSnapshot field `HasUnresolvedThreads bool`. In checkPR, after\ncalling ghpr.CheckStatus, additionally call a new ghpr.FetchUnresolvedThreadCount\nthat uses the GraphQL reviewThreads query (see Bug 2). If unresolved thread count\ntransitions from 0 to >0 (or PR is newly seen with unresolved threads), emit\nEventReviewChanges so reviewfix is triggered.\n\nghpr.CheckStatus should also be extended to include unresolved thread count alongside\nthe existing reviews/CI data.\n\n## Bug 2 â€” fetchReviewComments uses wrong API; misses inline threads and isResolved\n\nreviewfix.go fetchReviewComments: uses `gh pr view --json reviews,comments`.\nThe `comments` field in that API is PR-level general comments, NOT inline review\nthread comments (which live in `/repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{prNumber}/comments`\nor preferably via GraphQL reviewThreads). There is no isResolved field in the REST\nAPI â€” only GraphQL exposes it.\n\nFix: Replace fetchReviewComments with a GraphQL-based implementation:\n\n  gh api graphql -f query='\n  query($owner:String!, $repo:String!, $pr:Int!) {\n    repository(owner:$owner, name:$repo) {\n      pullRequest(number:$pr) {\n        reviewThreads(first:100) {\n          nodes {\n            id\n            isResolved\n            comments(first:1) {\n              nodes { path line body author { login } }\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }' -f owner=OWNER -f repo=REPO -F pr=NUMBER\n\nFilter nodes where isResolved: false. Map each to ReviewComment{ThreadID: node.id, ...}.\nThe owner/repo must be extracted from `git remote get-url origin` in the worktree.\n\nAlso fetch PR-level review body comments (non-thread) via:\n  gh pr view {number} --comments\nand include those that are not purely informational (heuristic: body length > 20 chars,\nnot an approval message).\n\n## Bug 3 â€” No thread resolution after fix\n\nAfter Smith successfully applies fixes and pushes, reviewfix returns without calling\nthe resolveReviewThread GraphQL mutation for the addressed threads.\n\nFix: After Smith exits with code 0, for each comment whose ThreadID is non-empty,\ncall:\n\n  gh api graphql -f query='\n  mutation($threadId:ID!) {\n    resolveReviewThread(input:{threadId:$threadId}) {\n      thread { isResolved }\n    }\n  }' -f threadId=\"{thread.id}\"\n\nAdd a resolveThread(ctx, worktreePath, threadID string) error helper in reviewfix.go.\nLog success/failure per thread but do not fail the overall FixResult if resolution\ncalls fail (thread resolution is best-effort).\n\n## Bug 4 â€” CI failure event not wired to a fix worker\n\nWhen bellows emits EventCIFailed, check daemon.go to confirm whether a handler\nactually spawns a Smith worker to fix it. If not (likely), add a ci_fix handler\nanalogous to the review_fix handler: spawn Smith with a prompt listing the failing\nCI checks (from gh pr checks output) and instruct it to fix build/test errors.\n\n## Implementation order\n\n1. Fix fetchReviewComments (Bug 2) â€” foundational for everything else\n2. Add resolveThread after fix (Bug 3)\n3. Fix bellows trigger to use unresolved thread count (Bug 1)\n4. Wire EventCIFailed to a ci fix smith in daemon.go (Bug 4)\n\n## GraphQL mutation reference (from Heimdall pr-fix skill)\n\nResolve thread:\n  gh api graphql -f query='mutation($threadId:ID!) { resolveReviewThread(input:{threadId:$threadId}) { thread { isResolved } } }' -f threadId=\"THREAD_NODE_ID\"\n\nQuery threads:\n  gh api graphql -f query='query($owner:String!, $repo:String!, $pr:Int!) { repository(owner:$owner,name:$repo) { pullRequest(number:$pr) { reviewThreads(first:100) { nodes { id isResolved comments(first:1) { nodes { path line body author { login } } } } } } } }' -f owner=OWNER -f repo=REPO -F pr=NUMBER\r\n\n\n## Working Directory\n\nYou are working in: c:\\source\\fhigit\\Forge\\.workers\\Forge-7ug\nBranch: forge/Forge-7ug\n"}
